Three persons have been reported killed and many injured in two attacks in Plateau State. In one of the attacks early Tuesday, gunmen killed a local miner and injured an unspecified number of persons in Yelwa Zangam area of Jos North council of the state. Two commuters were killed in the second assault in Bida Bidi area of Zaria Road in Jos, the state capital. Also, more people were injured and properties vandalised by the attackers.   Gunmen abduct 22 in Kaduna     Driver attacks LASTMA official with machete     COVID-19: IMF advises central banks on recovery   Information officer of Operation Safe Haven, Major Ishaku Takwa, confirmed the attacks in a statement. - Advertisement - “Also, in the late hours of same day, a vehicle conveying passengers was attacked along Jos-Jingir Road. An eyewitness report confirmed the presence of security personnel in the vicinity. Lalong, in a statement by his spokesman, Dr. Makut Simon Macham, commended security forces for their swift response, which helped to restore normalcy. He directed them to go after the attackers and arrest them. SPONSORED